 Lagos Shut Down Cubana Night Club For Operating Despite Ban On Night Clubs Due To COVID19 Cubana Night Club in Ikeja has been sealed off by the Lagos State Safety Commission on Saturday night, December 19 for not adhering to the COVID-19 protocols set by the state government. This comes after Sanwo-Olu, the Governor of Lagos State placed a ban on concert, street parties and nightclubs as parts of the measures to prevent the spread of Coronavirus in Lagos as it experiences the second wave of the pandemic. Some videos shared online showed patrons of the night club owned by Cubana Chief Priest being ordered to move out of the club after the Lagos State commissioner of Police, Hakeem Odumosu who lead the LSSC stormed the facility.